Supporters are flocking to Ace Magashule's stomping ground in Bloemfontein. Some are dressed in ANC party regalia, openly defying the ruling party's directive not to support alleged corrupt officials in court in party colours. Magashule faces charges of corruption linked to the Free State's asbestos saga. • Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. You may watch a recording above. BLOEMFONTEIN - ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule is appearing in the Bloemfontein magistrate's court. Magashule was formally arrested after handing himself over to the Hawks on Friday morning. READ: Magashule arrest being processed He's facing corruption charges for his alleged role in the Free State asbestos saga.